name: FishyC Mobile Game Creates Infinite Physics-Based Puzzler
blurb: FishyC Mobile Game Creates Infinite Multiplayer Physics-Based Puzzle Creator

rewards.reward: 1 in-game item powerup!!! We truly appreciate your support! Free access to our FORUM. For your decision to be a part of the history of gaming you will get a \u201cBRONZE FishyC BACKER BADGE on our Forum\u201d to proudly display next to your Forum ID. You\u2019re invited to communicate with other forum members \u2013 talk about the game, give us your ideas and find current development info that you won\u2019t find anywhere else!

4 in-game item powerups!!! You will get a \u201cBRONZE FishyC BACKER BADGE on our Forum\u201d to proudly display next to your Forum ID PLUS, a digital advance release of the game and cool Wallpaper for your devices! Start playing early and get your skills sharpened before the crowds jump in. Every newbie you play against will be wondering \u201cHow did they get that good so fast?!\u201d

7 in-game item powerups!!! All of the previous awards + your name in the \u201cSupporters\u201d credits at the end of the original game and the digital music used in the GAME! Show off to your friends how YOU were a part of the original gaming vision that changed the way people view physics-based puzzler mobile games.

All of the previous awards, + digital download of in-game SFX + your name in the \u201cSupporters\u201d credits at the end of the original game + your name in additional releases of the game\u2019s \u201cSupporters\u201d credits. Be an on-going part of gaming history and know that our development team is eternally grateful for your support.

All of the previous tier awards (But your Forum ID badge will be SILVER instead of Bronze) + you get to beta test the Puzzle Creator API for physics-based puzzler games and if any suggestion that you make is used \u2013 you will get a beta-testing development team acknowledgement in the game\u2019s credits. Become a true part of our team \u2013 where YOUR input will determine where our vision is ultimately headed!
All of the previous tier awards + digital .PDF of all sketches and animations of the game! WOW! Now that is way cool!

All of the previous tier awards (But your Forum ID badge will be GOLD instead of Silver) + a T-shirt (in the size of your choice) that identifies you as a backer of FISHYC. Imagine how cool that will look once the game takes off and a player sees you in it! Please add $20 dollars for International Shipping!

Beta Test the Actual Game on iOS (First Backers to Test FISHYC, you will need to register via http://testflightapp.com once we send you an email) a Limited Edition poster (suitable for framing) that will be SIGNED by the team members PLUS everything else in the previous tiers \u2013 Beta test Puzzle Creator Platform, the T-shirt, beta-test the game with in-credit acknowledgement, digital advance release of the game and GOLD Forum Badge.

A customized print containing YOUR image and the team member\u2019s signatures PLUS an iPad or iPod cover, the T-shirt, beta-test the game with in-credit acknowledgement, digital advance release of the game and Forum Badge.

ADD a new character (Either enemy, fish or object) with a name of your choosing \u2013 but it can\u2019t be NSFW (Not Suitable For the Workplace) -  PLUS an iPad or iPod cover, the T-shirt, beta-test the game with in-credit acknowledgement, digital advance release of the game and Forum Badge.

We will create an exclusive (and powerful) customized character designed to resemble YOU (with a name of your choosing \u2013 but it can\u2019t be NSFW, of course). This can be unlocked by up to 5 of your friends after they reach a specified level! Of course, we\u2019ll give you the code to unlock the character at the very beginning. PLUS the iPad or iPod cover, the T-shirt, beta-test the game with in-credit acknowledgement, digital advance release of the game and Forum Badge.

All previous tiers + you and a guest will have an invitation to the EXCLUSIVE GAME KICKOFF PARTY at our office (must be able to travel to and accommodate in Ottawa, Ontario Canada). Meet the team with plenty of photo ops for memories that will last forever. There\u2019s no better way to enjoy a gaming event!
